summary:
• FY2025 Results Announcement Date: 21 August 2025
  • Annual Report Publication Date: 30 September 2025
  • Annual Meeting Date: 13 November 2025

No material trading or capital markets information identified.

• FY25 Hydro Generation: 3,410 GWh (17% lower YoY), 4th lowest since 1980 due to 12th percentile Waikato catchment inflows.
  • Revised Mean Hydro Generation: Increased to 4,140 GWh annually from FY26 onward, driven by Karāpiro Rehabilitation Project (+16.5MW capacity, +32GWh/year) and Digital River AI platform.
  • Karāpiro Project Completion: Final unit replacement finishes Sep-25, concluding 3-year upgrade.
  • Market Prices: FY25 Auckland spot average $216/MWh; FY26-27 forward prices eased to $179/MWh.
  • Quarterly Hydrology: Ended at 79th percentile (improved from dry start), boosting FY26 storage.
  • Total FY25 Generation: 7,906 GWh (down 11% YoY), with declines in wind (-6%) and geothermal (-2%).

• Infratil Limited (IFT) to be added to S&P/ASX 200 Index, effective 23 July 2025 (pre-open).
  • Spartan Resources Limited (SPR) to be removed from the index on the same date due to acquisition by Ramelius Resources (RMS).

(No other material information identified)

Meridian Energy Monthly Operating Report (June 2025) – Key Takeaways

Operational Highlights

  • Hydro Storage:
  • National hydro storage increased from 94% to 104% of historical average (as of 14 July 2025).
  • South Island storage at 95%, North Island at 150% of historical average.

  • Waitaki catchment storage at 87%, Waiau at 130% of historical average.

  • Inflows & Generation:

  • June 2025 inflows: 111% of historical average.
  • Generation in June 2025: 6.1% YoY increase, with hydro and wind generation up.

  • Average generation price: 54.2% lower YoY ($121.0/MWh vs. $262.6/MWh).

  • Electricity Demand & Pricing:

  • National electricity demand in June: +1.4% YoY.
  • Futures prices decreased for all winter quarters in Q4.
  • NZ Aluminium Smelter (NZAS) average load: 530MW (vs. 394MW in June 2024).

Retail & Sales Performance

  • Retail sales volumes: +7.9% YoY in June 2025.
  • Residential: +12.7% YoY, large business: +15.2% YoY.
  • Customer growth: +9.6% YoY at end-Q4.

Key Agreement

  • NZAS demand response agreement terminated, targeting completion by 11 August 2025.

Financial Metrics

  • Q4 Generation: -8.8% YoY at 18.6% lower average price.
  • Operating costs: -0.2% YoY, capex: -16.5% YoY.

Market Outlook

  • NIWA forecasts warmer winter 2025 with above-average rainfall.

No material capital markets events (e.g., capital raises, trading halts) identified.
